 Tech Pratham – Deep Learning Course Website



 1. Project Overview

Project Name: Tech Pratham – Deep Learning Program Website
Client Type: EdTech / Online Learning Platform
Designer Role: UI/UX Designer (UX Strategy, Information Architecture, UI Design)
Platform: Responsive Web (Desktop, Tablet, Mobile)

 Objective

To design a high-conversion, learner-focused course landing experience that clearly communicates program value, builds credibility, and motivates users to enroll in the Deep Learning program.



 2. Problem Statement

Common issues in online course platforms:

. Overwhelming technical content for beginners
. Low trust in course outcomes
. Unclear learning paths and career benefits
. Poor conversion due to weak CTAs

Design Goal: Present complex deep learning concepts in a structured, beginner-friendly manner while emphasizing outcomes, career growth, and credibility to drive enrollments.



 3. Target Users & Personas

 Primary Users

1. Students & Fresh Graduates – Entering AI/ML field
2. Working Professionals – Career switch or upskilling
3. Data Analysts / Engineers – Advancing into Deep Learning

 User Needs

. Clear syllabus & duration
. Career outcomes & salary insights
. Proof of success (metrics & testimonials)
. Flexible learning schedule
. Transparent pricing



 4. User Journey

1. Landing on Course Page
   ↓
2. Understanding Course Value Proposition
   ↓
3. Reviewing Outcomes & Career Paths
   ↓
4. Exploring Curriculum & Learning Path
   ↓
5. Evaluating Testimonials & Metrics
   ↓
6. Enrollment Decision



 5. Information Architecture

 Primary Navigation

. Outcomes
. Career Paths
. Journey
. Skills
. Testimonials
. FAQ

 Conversion Actions

. Start Your Journey
. Enroll Now
. Download Syllabus



 6. Design System

 Color Palette

. Primary: Deep Blue / Purple (Technology & Trust)
. Accent: Yellow / Green (Growth & Success)
. Neutral: White & Light Grey

 Typography

. Headings: Bold, modern sans-serif
. Body Text: Regular, readable
. Metrics & Stats: Large, high-contrast fonts

 UI Principles

. Outcome-driven design
. Clear visual hierarchy
. Strong CTA emphasis
. Content chunking for readability



 7. Page-wise UX & UI Breakdown

 7.1 Hero Section

Purpose: Immediate value communication

Key Elements:

. Course headline (Transform Your Career with Deep Learning)
. Social proof quote
. Primary CTA buttons
. Key success metrics

UX Decisions:

. Metrics placed near hero for instant trust
. Dual CTA for exploration and action



 7.2 Course Highlights & Program Info

Content:

. Duration (12 weeks)
. Format (Part-time)
. Pricing & discount
. Pre-requisites

UX Strategy:

. Card-based layout
. Clear comparison of original vs discounted price
. Reduced friction with money-back guarantee



 7.3 Curriculum & Learning Path

Sections:

. Neural Network Foundations
. CNNs
. Sequence Models (RNNs, Transformers)
. Capstone Project

UX Rationale:

. Progressive disclosure (Expand to explore)
. Timeline-based mastery path
. Clear time allocation per module



 7.4 Your Path to Mastery

Purpose: Simplify complex learning journey

UX Decisions:

. Step-by-step numbered flow
. Visual progression indicators
. Focus on skill evolution



 7.5 Outcomes & Career Benefits

Content:

. Job placement success
. Salary increase
. Graduate success metrics

UX Goal:

. Reduce risk perception
. Emphasize ROI of learning



 7.6 Skills You’ll Master

Features:

. Skill clusters
. Proficiency indicators
. Industry relevance

UX Approach:

. Skill grouping
. Visual proficiency levels
. Non-overwhelming presentation



 7.7 Industry Applications

Industries Covered:

. Healthcare
. Finance
. Technology
. Marketing

UX Strategy:

. Real-world relevance mapping
. Broaden appeal across domains



 7.8 Career Opportunities

Roles Highlighted:

. Machine Learning Engineer
. AI Research Scientist
. AI Product Manager

UX Rationale:

. Salary ranges shown clearly
. Market demand indicators
. Exploration CTA per role



 7.9 Testimonials & Success Stories

Purpose: Trust & credibility

UX Decisions:

. Human-centered storytelling
. Repetition for social proof



 7.10 FAQ Section

Goal: Address objections

UX Strategy:

. Expandable accordion format
. Clear, concise answers



 7.11 Final Conversion Section

Elements:

. Program summary
. Benefits recap
. Pricing & guarantee
. Strong CTA

UX Goal:

. Reinforce confidence
. Remove last-minute hesitation



 8. Accessibility & Usability Considerations

. Clear readable font sizes
. Mobile-first responsiveness
. High contrast CTAs
. Simple language for beginners



 9. Conversion Optimization Strategy

. Repeated CTAs across sections
. Outcome-first messaging
. Social proof near decision points
. Risk reversal (money-back guarantee)



 10. Tools Used

. Design: Figma
. Prototyping: Interactive web prototype
. UX Research: EdTech & course platform benchmarking



 11. Future Enhancements

. Personalized learning recommendations
. AI mentor chatbot
. Student dashboard integration
. Community discussion forums



 12. Conclusion

This UI/UX design balances educational clarity with strong marketing principles. By focusing on outcomes, structured learning paths, and trust-building elements, the design effectively converts visitors into confident learners.



Designed by: Sanskrati Agrawal
Role: UI/UX Designer
